				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">You're right.  
<br />

<br />
I made 5th level and only got ONE spell.  I was expecting more, like the spell list you get every 4 levels in EQ.   
<br />

<br />
The one Nightshade spell is good at luring a monster to me, rather than my running up to it and I was able to cast it twice before switching to attack mode.  The spell damage tended to do around 6 points then 13 points and didnt take very much mana.
<br />

<br />
However, when its safe to sneak-up behind your opponent and Backstab, I can do 18 or so in one strike, and we DO have Stealth so we can sneak-up..  The spell seemed a bit pointless at level 5 anyway..
<br />

<br />
Anyone have experience with using magic effectively at higher levels?
<br />

<br />
Nightshade seems like a rogue with the ability to do a magic poke-your-foe to get his attention.  Heh.  We might be better off just using a bow for the similar result.
<br />

<br />
Im going to remake my little guy with extra quickness, Con and Agility -- no extra INT.
<br />

<br />
Anyone figure out if quickness does anything?  I guess I would have to play a quick little fighter then play a big strong viking-type to see if there is a difference.
<br />
Same question with Agility...</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
